<div class="wrapper-content">
  <div class="full-up formatting">
    <h2>Visualizing School Change</h2>
    <p>Effective teaching is the result of daily practice in front of students and regular professional development. With Verso, teachers could easily evaluate student thinking in minute detail. Data was gathered for each activity to help teachers pinpoint where help was most needed. Campus unifies engagement statistics for an entire school. So instead of peering through the narrow scope of individual activities, the expanded perspective of Campus helps identify school-wide challenges.</p>

    <div class="media-centeralign">
      <img src="/img/case-study/campus/verso-campus-activetime-v2.svg" alt="Time of day most active">
      <span class="caption">Teachers can better facilitate learning by knowing when students engage with activities.</span>
    </div>

    <h2>Actionable Insights</h2>
    <p>We see analytics as an opportunity to start constructive conversations. Our process began with researching teacher, department and administrator objectives to discover how to frame data in a way that would address real user needs.</p>

    <p>We engineered an insight engine that processed data in realtime to identify high-level patterns and highlight outliers based on research. We surfaced these findings to users in the form of natural language insights paired with prompts to act. For instance, <em>"Tom's engagement time dipped slightly, keep an eye out"</em>. Our faceted analytics experience further enabled users to easily filter & segment engagement by class, teacher, subject, or grade level.</p>

    <p style="margin-bottom:0;">Our integrated product development process yielded Campus, a education product that reveals proven teaching strategies, highlights areas for improvement, and delivers recommendations for continued success.</p>
  </div>
</div>

